{"nodes":[{"pos":[32,69],"content":"What's new archive | Microsoft Intune","needQuote":true,"nodes":[{"content":"What's new archive | Microsoft Intune","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[401,414],"content":"December 2015","linkify":"December 2015","nodes":[{"content":"December 2015","pos":[0,13]}]},{"pos":[419,466],"content":"Changes and updates to Microsoft Company Portal","linkify":"Changes and updates to Microsoft Company Portal","nodes":[{"content":"Changes and updates to Microsoft Company Portal","pos":[0,47]}]},{"content":"The following changes have been made to the Company Portal in this release.","pos":[467,542]},{"content":"Android Company Portal app","pos":[546,572]},{"content":"The following changes have been made to comply with new Google requirements.","pos":[576,652]},{"content":"On Android 6.0 and above devices, two new messages are displayed to users:","pos":[653,727]},{"content":"Allow Company Portal to make and manage phone calls?","pos":[730,782]},{"content":"Allow Company Portal to access photos, media, and files on your device?","pos":[785,856]},{"content":"See the following tables for details about these two messages.","pos":[858,920]},{"content":"Message text","pos":[924,936]},{"content":"Allow Company Portal to make and manage phone calls?","pos":[939,991]},{"content":"Meaning of message","pos":[1014,1032]},{"content":"Enables the user's device phone number and IMEI to be sent to the Intune service and appear in the Admin console on the Hardware page.","pos":[1040,1174]},{"content":"NOTE: The Company Portal app never makes or manages phone calls!","pos":[1189,1253]},{"content":"The message text is controlled by Google and cannot be changed.","pos":[1256,1319]},{"content":"To see the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Hardware<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, go to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Groups<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>All mobile devices<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph2\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Device<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>s.","pos":[1330,1416],"source":"To see the **Hardware** page, go to **Groups** > **All mobile devices** > **Device**s."},{"content":"Select the user's device, and go to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>View Properties<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Hardware<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[1417,1488],"source":" Select the user's device, and go to **View Properties** > **Hardware**."},{"content":"Where and when message appears","pos":[1493,1523]},{"content":"The message appears when users sign in to the Company Portal app for the first time to start enrolling their device.","pos":[1527,1643]},{"content":"What happens if users allow access","pos":[1654,1688]},{"content":"The device's phone number and IMEI will appear on the Hardware page in the Admin console.","pos":[1693,1782]},{"content":"What happens if users deny access","pos":[1794,1827]},{"content":"They can continue to use the Company Portal app and enroll their device, but the users's device phone number and IMEI will be blank on the Hardware page in the Admin console.","pos":[1834,2008]},{"content":"The second time that users sign in to the Company Portal app after denying access, the message displays a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Never ask again<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> check box that users can select so that the message never shows again.","pos":[2026,2222],"source":" The second time that users sign in to the Company Portal app after denying access, the message displays a **Never ask again** check box that users can select so that the message never shows again."},{"content":"If users allow but then later deny access, the message appears the next time users sign in to the Company Portal app after enrollment.","pos":[2232,2366]},{"content":"If users later decide to allow access, they can go to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Apps<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph2\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Company Portal<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph3\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Permissions<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph4\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>Phone<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept>, and then turn on the permission.","pos":[2376,2538],"source":"If users later decide to allow access, they can go to **Settings** > **Apps** > **Company Portal** > **Permissions** > **Phone**, and then turn on the permission."},{"content":"More information","pos":[2539,2555]},{"content":"For your users: <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Sign in to the Company Portal<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt502762.aspx#BKMK_andr_signin_cp)</ept>","pos":[2563,2683],"source":"For your users: [Sign in to the Company Portal](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt502762.aspx#BKMK_andr_signin_cp)"},{"content":"For IT Pros: The information in this table is also in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Helping your users understand Company Portal app messages<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn948527.aspx#BKMK_help_users_understd_msgs)</ept>","pos":[2695,2891],"source":"For IT Pros: The information in this table is also in [Helping your users understand Company Portal app messages](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn948527.aspx#BKMK_help_users_understd_msgs)"},{"content":"Message text","pos":[2896,2908]},{"content":"Allow Company Portal to access photos, media, and files on your device?","pos":[2911,2982]},{"content":"Meaning of message","pos":[3005,3023]},{"content":"Enables the device to write data logs to the device's SD card, which enables logs to be moved by using a USB cable.","pos":[3031,3146]},{"content":"NOTE: The Company Portal app never accesses users' photos, media, and files!","pos":[3161,3237]},{"content":"The message text is controlled by Google and cannot be changed.","pos":[3240,3303]},{"content":"Where and when message appears","pos":[3309,3339]},{"pos":[3343,3428],"content":"The message appears when users tap <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Send Data<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to send data logs to their IT admin.","source":"The message appears when users tap **Send Data** to send data logs to their IT admin."},{"content":"What happens if users allow access","pos":[3439,3473]},{"content":"The logs will be copied to the SD card.","pos":[3478,3517]},{"content":"What happens if users deny access","pos":[3529,3562]},{"content":"They can still send data logs, but the logs won't be copied to the device's SD card.","pos":[3569,3653]},{"content":"The second time that users sign in to the Company Portal app after denying access, the message displays a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Never ask again<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> check box that users can select so that the message never shows again.","pos":[3671,3867],"source":" The second time that users sign in to the Company Portal app after denying access, the message displays a **Never ask again** check box that users can select so that the message never shows again."},{"content":"If users allow but then later deny access, the message appears the next time users try to send logs.","pos":[3877,3977]},{"content":"If users later decide to allow access, they can go to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Apps<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph2\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Company Portal<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph3\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Permissions<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph4\"> &gt; </ph><bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>Storage<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept>, and then turn on the permission.","pos":[3987,4151],"source":"If users later decide to allow access, they can go to **Settings** > **Apps** > **Company Portal** > **Permissions** > **Storage**, and then turn on the permission."},{"content":"More information","pos":[4152,4168]},{"content":"For your users: <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Send diagnostic data logs to your IT admin using email<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt502762.aspx#BKMK_andr_send_diag_logs)</ept>","pos":[4176,4326],"source":"For your users: [Send diagnostic data logs to your IT admin using email](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt502762.aspx#BKMK_andr_send_diag_logs)"},{"content":"For IT Pros: The information in this table is also in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Helping your users understand Company Portal app messages<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn948527.aspx#BKMK_help_users_understd_msgs)</ept>","pos":[4338,4534],"source":"For IT Pros: The information in this table is also in [Helping your users understand Company Portal app messages](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn948527.aspx#BKMK_help_users_understd_msgs)"},{"content":"iOS Company Portal app","pos":[4542,4564]},{"content":"Users can now use Microsoft Outlook or other mail apps to send diagnostic logs to the IT administrator.","pos":[4569,4672]},{"content":"Previously, only the native app could be used.","pos":[4673,4719]},{"content":"Support has been improved for Apple's Device Enrollment Program (DEP) and corporate-enrolled devices.","pos":[4722,4823]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>You are asked to identify your device when you're trying to enroll<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt598622.aspx#BKMK_ios_id_your_device)</ept>.","pos":[4824,4987],"source":" For details, see [You are asked to identify your device when you're trying to enroll](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt598622.aspx#BKMK_ios_id_your_device)."},{"content":"In the user's list of enrolled devices, a green check mark now appears next to the device that the user is currently using.","pos":[4990,5113]},{"content":"Before this check mark was added, users couldn't tell which enrolled device they were using.","pos":[5114,5206]},{"content":"Windows Company Portal app","pos":[5210,5236]},{"content":"Microsoft automatically collects anonymous data about the performance and use of the company portal to improve Microsoft products and services.","pos":[5240,5383]},{"content":"End users can turn off data collection by using the Usage Data setting on their device, but administrators have no control over the data collection and cannot change the end userâ€™s selection for this setting.","pos":[5384,5592]},{"pos":[5599,5612],"content":"November 2015","linkify":"November 2015","nodes":[{"content":"November 2015","pos":[0,13]}]},{"pos":[5617,5631],"content":"App management","linkify":"App management","nodes":[{"content":"App management","pos":[0,14]}]},{"content":"Intune supports mobile application management (MAM) policies that help prevent corporate data from being leaked to consumer apps or services.","pos":[5632,5773]},{"content":"Historically, these policies would only be enforced on mobile apps running on devices that were also enrolled for mobile device management (MDM) into Intune.","pos":[5774,5931]},{"content":"With this month's update, Intune is expanding its MAM capabilities to new classes of devices.","pos":[5933,6026]},{"content":"In addition to devices enrolled into Intune, you can now enforce MAM policies on:","pos":[6027,6108]},{"content":"devices managed by any other device management (MDM) solution","pos":[6111,6172]},{"content":"device that are not enrolled into any device management system, typically bring-your-own (BYO) devices","pos":[6175,6277]},{"content":"You can find more information about these new MAM capabilities in the following blog posts:","pos":[6279,6370]},{"content":"Enhancing managed mobile productivity","pos":[6374,6411]},{"content":"Announcing new Microsoft Enterprise Mobility capabilities","pos":[6522,6579]},{"content":"Additionally, here are some highlights and additional information about Intune's MAM features:","pos":[6688,6782]},{"content":"Corporate data is isolated from consumer data within apps enlightened for Intune including Office Mobile apps, third-party apps that have adopted the Intune SDK, or line-of-business apps wrapped by Intune.","pos":[6785,6990]},{"content":"Company data can be shared (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>cut/copy/paste<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>) across company apps, while preventing the sharing of company data into personal apps.","pos":[6993,7126],"source":"Company data can be shared (**cut/copy/paste**) across company apps, while preventing the sharing of company data into personal apps."},{"content":"Read <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How MAM policies protect app data<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627825.aspx)</ept> for more details.","pos":[7127,7238],"source":" Read [How MAM policies protect app data](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627825.aspx) for more details."},{"content":"This example scenario, <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Using Microsoft Word app for work and personal tasks<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627827.aspx)</ept>, shows how sharing company data into personal apps is prevented.","pos":[7239,7434],"source":" This example scenario, [Using Microsoft Word app for work and personal tasks](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627827.aspx), shows how sharing company data into personal apps is prevented."},{"content":"Key data loss prevention policies like per-App PIN, save-as controls, and managed data sharing between apps.","pos":[7437,7545]},{"content":"Read <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create and deploy mobile app management policies with Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627829.aspx)</ept> to see a list of all the policies.","pos":[7546,7711],"source":" Read [Create and deploy mobile app management policies with Microsoft Intune](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627829.aspx) to see a list of all the policies."},{"content":"Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, OneNote, and OneDrive for Business all have these new capabilities and can be managed with and without device enrollment.","pos":[7714,7869]},{"content":"The data loss protection capabilities are natively built into the standard Office apps in the Apple Store or the Google Play store, and do not require app wrapping or sideloading.","pos":[7870,8049]},{"content":"To learn how to get started, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Get started with mobile app management policies in the Azure portal<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627830.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[8052,8208],"source":"To learn how to get started, see [Get started with mobile app management policies in the Azure portal](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627830.aspx)."},{"content":"To learn how to configure and deploy mobile app management policies, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create and deploy mobile app management policies with Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627829.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[8209,8408],"source":" To learn how to configure and deploy mobile app management policies, see [Create and deploy mobile app management policies with Microsoft Intune](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627829.aspx)."},{"content":"When end-users authenticate to the app with their corporate credentials, the data loss protection capabilities are automatically set up.","pos":[8411,8547]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>End-user experience for apps associated with Microsoft Intune mobile app management policies<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627827.aspx)</ept> topic has some example scenarios for accessing OneDrive on iOS and Android devices.","pos":[8548,8783],"source":" The [End-user experience for apps associated with Microsoft Intune mobile app management policies](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627827.aspx) topic has some example scenarios for accessing OneDrive on iOS and Android devices."},{"content":"Works on both iOS and Android devices.","pos":[8786,8824]},{"pos":[8826,9022],"content":"The list of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft apps you can use with Microsoft Intune mobile application management policies<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn708489.aspx)</ept> has been 