ur devices with Microsoft Intune policies<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn646984.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[10527,10662],"source":" See [Manage settings and features on your devices with Microsoft Intune policies](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn646984.aspx)."},{"pos":[10664,10804],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>New compliance policy settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> The following new security and system policy settings have been added to the list of compliance policies:","source":"**New compliance policy settings**\nThe following new security and system policy settings have been added to the list of compliance policies:"},{"content":"To make sure that Windows 8.1 or later devices that access your company resources have the latest updates installed, use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Require automatic updates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> setting.","pos":[10807,10970],"source":"To make sure that Windows 8.1 or later devices that access your company resources have the latest updates installed, use the **Require automatic updates** setting."},{"content":"You can also specify the type of updates to be automatically installed -- either all updates marked as important to be installed, or all updates marked important or recommended.","pos":[10971,11148]},{"content":"For the full list of compliance policy settings, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage device compliance policies for Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn705843.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[11149,11312],"source":" For the full list of compliance policy settings, see [Manage device compliance policies for Microsoft Intune](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/dn705843.aspx)."},{"pos":[11315,11634],"content":"The new <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Require a password when the device returns from the idle state<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> setting combined with the existing <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Minutes of inactivity before password is required<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> setting allows you to create a compliance setting that requires the end-user to enter a password to use a device that has been inactive for a certain time.","source":"The new **Require a password when the device returns from the idle state** setting combined with the existing **Minutes of inactivity before password is required** setting allows you to create a compliance setting that requires the end-user to enter a password to use a device that has been inactive for a certain time."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>New conditional access policy options<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You can apply conditional access policies to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>all users<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> in either new or existing conditional access policies.","pos":[11636,11791],"source":"**New conditional access policy options**\nYou can apply conditional access policies to **all users** in either new or existing conditional access policies."},{"content":"All users licensed for Intune and Office 365 will be required to enroll their devices, and if the device platform is not supported by Intune, access is blocked for client applications using <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Active Directory authentication based sign-in (modern authentication)<ept id=\"p1\">](https://blogs.office.com/2014/11/12/office-2013-updated-authentication-enabling-multi-factor-authentication-saml-identity-providers/)</ept>.","pos":[11792,12188],"source":" All users licensed for Intune and Office 365 will be required to enroll their devices, and if the device platform is not supported by Intune, access is blocked for client applications using [Active Directory authentication based sign-in (modern authentication)](https://blogs.office.com/2014/11/12/office-2013-updated-authentication-enabling-multi-factor-authentication-saml-identity-providers/)."},{"content":"You can also specify that the conditional access policy applies to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>all platforms<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[12190,12275],"source":"You can also specify that the condi